Merge pull request #39 from mozilla/fetch-openid-configuration r=@vladikoff

feat(interface): Add `launchWebExtensionFlow`, get URLs from oidc discovery doc

feat(interface): Add `launchWebExtensionFlow`, get URLs from oidc discovery doc

This is two things rolled into 1.

First, only specify the content server URL, from there fetch
any necessary URLs from the OIDC discovery doc at ./well-known/openid-configuration.
This eliminates hard coding any URLs.

Next, add a new method, `launchWebExtensionFlow` that does not
request scoped keys. The old method, `launchWebExtensionKeysFlow`
still exists and still acts how it did previously.
